---
import Layout from '../../components/layout/Layout.astro';
import { SITE_NAME, SITE_URL } from '../../config';
import { buildBreadcrumbSchema } from '../../lib/seo';

const title = 'Cookie Policy - Types, Purpose and How to Manage Them';
const description = 'What cookies we use, their purpose and duration. Step-by-step instructions to manage and disable cookies in your browser to control your privacy settings.';

const schemas = [
  buildBreadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', url: '/en/' },
    { name: 'Cookie Policy', url: '/en/cookie-policy/' },
  ]),
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} schema={schemas} locale="en">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-8">
    <nav class="mb-6 text-sm text-medium-gray">
      <a href="/en/" class="hover:text-brand">Home</a> / <span class="text-charcoal dark:text-gray-200">Cookie Policy</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold text-charcoal md:text-4xl dark:text-gray-100">Cookie Policy</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-dark-gray dark:text-gray-300 space-y-6">
      <p><em>Last updated: June {new Date().getFullYear()}</em></p>

      <p>
        At <strong>{SITE_NAME}</strong> ({SITE_URL}), we value your privacy. This cookie policy explains
        what cookies and storage technologies we use and which we do not, in compliance with the GDPR
        (Regulation EU 2016/679), the Spanish LOPDGDD (Organic Law 3/2018), and Article 22.2 of the LSSI-CE.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal dark:text-gray-100">1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
      <p>
        Cookies are small text files that websites store on your computer or mobile device when you visit
        them. They are widely used to make websites function correctly, improve user experience, and provide
        information to website owners. Cookies can be classified into several categories: strictly necessary
        cookies, functional cookies, analytics cookies, and marketing cookies.
      </p>
      <p>
        European legislation, particularly the ePrivacy Directive and the GDPR, requires websites to inform
        users about cookie usage and, in many cases, obtain consent before placing cookies. Strictly
        necessary cookies are exempt from this requirement and may be placed without consent.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal dark:text-gray-100">2. Does This Website Use Cookies?</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>No, we do not use tracking cookies.</strong> No advertising cookies, third-party analytics
        cookies, profiling cookies, or cookies for tracking user behaviour are placed. This means your
        browsing activity is not tracked and no personal profiles are created based on your visit.
      </p>
      <p>
        We only place strictly necessary technical cookies required for the basic functionality of the
        website. These cookies do not require prior consent under Article 22.2 of the LSSI-CE and
        Article 5(3) of the ePrivacy Directive, as they are strictly necessary to provide the service
        requested by the user.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal dark:text-gray-100">3. Plausible Analytics: Cookie-Free</h2>
      <p>
        For website statistics, we use
        <a href="https://plausible.io" class="text-brand hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Plausible Analytics</a>,
        a privacy-friendly, open-source alternative to Google Analytics that:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
        <li><strong>Places no cookies</strong> of any kind</li>
        <li><strong>Collects no personal data</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Stores no IP addresses</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Uses no fingerprinting</strong> or other persistent identification techniques</li>
        <li><strong>Does not track</strong> users across sessions or websites</li>
        <li>Is fully <strong>GDPR-compliant</strong> without requiring a cookie banner</li>
        <li>Processes data on servers within the <strong>European Union</strong></li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Plausible collects exclusively aggregated and anonymous statistics such as page views, traffic
        sources, countries of origin, device types and browsers. This data cannot be traced back to
        individual visitors. More information:
        <a href="https://plausible.io/data-policy" class="text-brand hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://plausible.io/data-policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal dark:text-gray-100">4. Functional Storage (localStorage)</h2>
      <p>
        Our website stores your theme preference (light or dark mode) and potential language preferences in
        your browser using <strong>localStorage</strong>. This is not a cookie but a local storage method
        provided by the HTML5 standard. localStorage differs from cookies in important ways:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
        <li>Data is <strong>not sent to our servers</strong> with page requests</li>
        <li>Data is <strong>not traceable</strong> to you as a person</li>
        <li>You can delete the data through your browser settings</li>
        <li>The storage is strictly necessary for website functionality</li>
        <li>No information is shared with third parties</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Since localStorage is not a cookie and data is never sent to external servers, it falls under the
        exemption for strictly necessary technical storage and no prior consent is required.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal dark:text-gray-100">5. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        Our website may load web fonts from third-party content delivery networks. When you access a page,
        your browser loads the required fonts from external servers, which may receive your IP address as
        part of the standard HTTP request. This usage is based on our legitimate interest (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR)
        in a uniform and attractive presentation of our website.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do not integrate any other third-party services that profile users. There are no social media
        buttons, advertising widgets, remarketing services, or other tools that allow third parties to
        track users.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal dark:text-gray-100">6. Cookie Banner</h2>
      <p>
        Since we do not use tracking cookies, analytics cookies, or marketing cookies, a cookie banner or
        consent mechanism is not legally required under the LSSI-CE and ePrivacy Directive. Nevertheless,
        we inform you fully and transparently through this policy, in line with the principles of
        transparency and fairness of the GDPR.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal dark:text-gray-100">7. How to Manage Cookies in Your Browser</h2>
      <p>
        Most web browsers allow you to manage cookies through their settings. You can reject cookies,
        delete existing ones, or set your browser to alert you when a cookie is placed. Refer to your
        browser's help for specific instructions:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
        <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:underline">Google Chrome</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/cookies-information-websites-store-on-your-computer" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:underline">Mozilla Firefox</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:underline">Safari</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:underline">Microsoft Edge</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Please note that blocking all cookies may affect the functionality of some websites.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal dark:text-gray-100">8. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Under the GDPR and LOPDGDD, you have the right to be informed about the use of cookies and storage
        technologies. Since we do not collect personal data through cookies, most GDPR rights are not
        applicable in practice. You always have the right to reject cookies, delete localStorage data, lodge
        a complaint with the AEPD, and contact us with questions about our cookie policy.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal dark:text-gray-100">9. Changes and Contact</h2>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to modify this cookie policy to reflect changes in our practices or applicable
        law. The current version is always available on this page. For questions, contact us at:<br>
        Email: <a href="mailto:contacto@elsueldoneto.es" class="text-brand hover:underline">contacto@elsueldoneto.es</a>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal dark:text-gray-100">10. Related Pages</h2>
      <p>
        See also our <a href="/en/privacy-policy/" class="text-brand hover:underline">privacy policy</a> and
        our <a href="/en/legal-notice/" class="text-brand hover:underline">legal notice</a> for more
        information about how we handle your data and the legal aspects of our website.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
